<subSubSection id="FC8E653B874BB1111CEC5530F655FB34" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0874BB1111CEC5530F6DFFC72" blockId="4.[1973,2567,802,1225]" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2874BB1111CEC5530F7C4FCC2" bold="true" box="[1973,2128,802,831]" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB11113285530F86EFC9A" authority="Thompson, 1815" authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="1815" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">Mus anomalus Thompson, 1815</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED874BB111134B5558F6D3FC72" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894331" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">“Trinidad... [near] St. Anne’s barracks,” Trinidad and Tobago</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0874BB1111CEC5587F655FB34" blockId="4.[1973,2567,802,1225]" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">
With the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB111124A5587F593FC4B" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1868" box="[2323,2567,917,950]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="desmarestianus">H. desmarestianus</taxonomicName>
in the north-western corner of Colombia, the South American spiny pocket mice all belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB11113EA5219F6BBFBD1" authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="1815" box="[2227,2351,1035,1068]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">anomalus</taxonomicName>
species group: 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB1111CEF5229F7F9FBA9" authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="1815" box="[1974,2157,1083,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">H. anomalus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB11113D55229F6D8FBA9" authorityName="Anderson &amp; Gutierrez" authorityYear="2009" box="[2188,2380,1083,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="catopterius">H. catopterius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB11112325229F66BFBA9" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[2411,2559,1083,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oasicus">H. oasicus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB1111CEE5270F7C4FB86" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[1975,2128,1122,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">H. australis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB11113C65270F684FB86" authorityName="R. P. Anderson &amp; Jarrin-Valladares" authorityYear="2002" box="[2207,2320,1122,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="teleus">H. teleus</taxonomicName>
. Only 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33874BB11112375270F593FB86" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[2414,2567,1122,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Heteromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">H. australis</taxonomicName>
exists outside of South America in eastern Panama. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
